        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded mb-3">
            <p>Yes, I may be showing my age, but PLC2-5 systems were incredibly reliable. However, we did encounter a few issues with the SLC's after about 6 years of use. The plastic cases of the PV550's began to deteriorate, the HMI psu had a tendency to fail, and the PLC's developed various faults such as cracked solder joints on the backplane and psu failures leading to ram corruption or loss of programming. We also experienced power supply failures with the later PV+ models, as well as frequent drive failures. To address these issues, we replaced some drives with Mitsubishi and others with different models, all of which proved to be more reliable. Eventually, we replaced all drives with Mitsubishi and upgraded the HMI's to Beijers, after which we experienced no further problems except for the occasional mishap with operators using inappropriate tools to navigate the interfaces.</p>
